Overview

This project is a portable health monitoring system designed to measure and display a user's heart rate (BPM) and blood oxygen saturation (SpO₂) levels in real time. The system utilizes the MAX30102 Pulse Oximeter Sensor and an Arduino Uno microcontroller to process physiological data and present the results on an OLED/LCD display.

The device offers an affordable and efficient solution for continuous health monitoring, making it suitable for personal use, healthcare facilities, rural health centers, and emergency screening applications.

