Working Principle

The system operates using Photoplethysmography (PPG), a non-invasive optical technique used to detect blood volume changes in the microvascular bed of tissue.

The MAX30102 sensor emits red and infrared light into the fingertip and measures the reflected light intensity. These signals are processed by the Arduino Uno, which calculates:

Heart Rate (Beats Per Minute)
Blood Oxygen Saturation (SpO₂ Percentage)

The processed values are then displayed on an OLED or LCD screen for real-time monitoring.

